# MCP Tools Usage Standards

> **Related Rules**: See [Type Safety](./typescript.mdc), [Security Standards](./security.mdc), [API Design](./api-design.mdc)

## Context7

- Technical documentation retrieval tool, query official documentation and best practices before implementation
- Usage: `@C7` or `@Context7`
- Used for querying Angular, TypeScript, ng-alain and other technical documentation

## Sequential Thinking

- Complex problem analysis and decision making, used for architecture design and root cause analysis
- Usage: `@S7` or `@Sequential Thinking`
- Used for structured thinking on complex problems

## Software Planning Tool

- Must be used for Level 3+ complex tasks, used for task planning and tracking
- Usage: `@SPT` or `@Software Planning Tool`
- Used for task decomposition and tracking of large features

## Memory

- Record architecture decisions, technical debt, configurations, and test results
- Regularly clean up redundant memories

## Supabase MCP

- All database operations must go through `@SUPABASE` MCP tool
- Use Supabase MCP to regularly check database structure
- Use Supabase MCP tools to generate TypeScript type definitions (see [Type Safety](./typescript.mdc))
- Database operations need RLS checks enabled (see [Security Standards](./security.mdc))
- Use Repository pattern to encapsulate data access (see [API Design Standards](./api-design.mdc))

